@page
@model MegaForm.Samples.CorporateWeb.Pages.DetailsModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Details";
}

<section class="content-page">
    <div class="container">
        <h1>How it works</h1>
        <p>
            The <strong>CorporateWeb</strong> sample is a typical ASP.NET Core
            Razor Pages application. It references the
            <code>MegaForm.AspNetCore.Component</code> NuGet package and calls
            three integration points:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><code>builder.AddMegaForm(...)</code> — registers services, auth, MVC and the database.</li>
            <li><code>app.EnsureMegaFormDatabaseReady()</code> — creates the MegaForm schema.</li>
            <li><code>app.UseMegaForm()</code> — enables static assets, middleware and controllers.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            The contact page then uses the <code>&lt;megaform&gt;</code> TagHelper
            to embed a published form that was seeded when the app first started.
        </p>
        <p>
            Because MegaForm runs inside the same host, there is no external
            server to configure. Forms, submissions and the admin console are all
            available under the same application URL.
        </p>
        <div class="cta-row">
            <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/Contact">See the contact form</a>
            <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/">Back to home</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
